How to configure ruff for sorting import. Now I don't see any options for organizing import

To configure Ruff for import sorting, you can expand your ruff configuration in `pyproject.toml`. Here's how you can enhance the configuration to better control import sorting:

```toml
[tool.ruff]
# Enable rules
select = [
    "I",    # isort
    "F",    # pyflakes
    "E",    # pycodestyle errors
    "W",    # pycodestyle warnings
]

# Ruff's isort configuration
[tool.ruff.isort]
combine-as-imports = true
# Add these additional settings for more control:
force-sort-within-sections = true
relative-imports-order = "closest-to-furthest"
known-first-party = ["egreen"]  # Add your project's main package name
known-third-party = ["django", "rest_framework"]
sections = [
    "FUTURE",
    "STDLIB",
    "THIRDPARTY",
    "DJANGO",
    "FIRSTPARTY",
    "LOCAL",
]
section-order = [
    "FUTURE",
    "STDLIB",
    "THIRDPARTY",
    "DJANGO",
    "FIRSTPARTY",
    "LOCAL",
]

[tool.ruff.per-file-ignores]
# Ignore specific rules for specific files if needed
"__init__.py" = ["F401"]  # Ignore unused imports in __init__.py files
```

This configuration:
1. Enables import sorting (`"I"`) along with other useful checks
2. Configures how imports should be grouped and sorted
3. Specifies known first-party and third-party packages
4. Defines custom sections and their order
5. Sets up handling of relative imports

You can also add a task in your `.zed/tasks.json` to run Ruff:

```json
{
    "label": "Format imports with Ruff",
    "command": "ruff check --fix .",
    "reveal": "always"
}
```

To use Ruff for auto-formatting in Zed, you can update your `.zed/settings.json`:

```json
{
    "languages": {
        "Python": {
            "formatter": {
                "external": { "command": "ruff", "arguments": ["format", "--stdin-filename", "file.py", "-"] }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Remember to install Ruff if you haven't already (it's already in your dev dependencies).
